An index in SQL is a data structure that improves the speed of data retrieval operations in a database.
Instead of scanning an entire table, SQL uses indexes to quickly find relevant rows, significantly improving query speed.

Lazy and Eager are fetch strategies in Hibernate/JPA that define when related entities are loaded from the database.
Lazy fetching means related entities are loaded only when they are accessed,
Eager fetching means related entities are loaded immediately along with the parent entity.
Default Fetch Types
@OneToMany, @ManyToMany → LAZY
@ManyToOne, @OneToOne → EAGER

